  "prompt": "I got 168 in JEE (Main) 2016. How much score should I expect (rough range) according to my potential , in BITSAT 2016 ?",
  "response": "It's difficult to provide an exact range for your potential BITSAT score based solely on your JEE Main score, as these exams differ in format, style, and difficulty. However, I can offer some insight and a rough estimation based on general trends observed among students.\n\nThe JEE Main and BITSAT exams are both competitive, but BITSAT is typically considered to test speed and accuracy over a larger number of relatively easier questions compared to JEE Main. Students often find that their BITSAT score is somewhat higher than their JEE Main score, proportionately, due to the nature of the test. \n\nTo set expectations, here is a rough guide:\n- If you were well-prepared for JEE Main and you adapt well to the BITSAT style with its focus on speed and accuracy, you can expect your BITSAT score to be relatively higher than your JEE Main score when normalized for the different total scores.\n- Candidates scoring around 150-180 in JEE Main have been known to score anywhere between 250-320 in BITSAT, depending on their preparation and exam conditions.\n\nRemember that individual performance can vary, and these numbers are just a rough guide. Your actual BITSAT score will depend on many factors, including your comfort with the exam format and your ability to manage time effectively during the test.",
